'''Cancer Campus''' is a research and innovative campus in [[oncology]] located in [[Villejuif]], close to [[Paris]], and launched in April 2006.<ref>{{fr}}[http://www.unicancer.fr/actualites/actualites-centres/inauguration-de-villejuif-bio-park-pepiniere-d’entreprises-de-cancer-campus Première pierre de Cancer Campus]</ref> It is devoted to help to fight [[cancer]].

It is backed by the expertise of the ''[[Institut Gustave Roussy]]'' and other health institutions and research of the ''[[Ile-de-France]]'' [[region of France|region]].<ref>{{fr}}[http://www.leparisien.fr/cachan-94230/une-feuille-de-route-pour-cancer-campus-10-12-2011-1761170.php Une feuille de route pour Cancer Campus]</ref>

The goal is to bring together on a single research campus (clinical and academic, public and private) companies, high-level training, a set of partners forming a "biocluster" part of the [[Business cluster|cluster]] [[Medicen]].<ref>{{fr}}[http://www.leparisien.fr/val-de-marne-94/c-est-parti-pour-cancer-campus-17-11-2011-1724436.php C'est parti pour Cancer Campus]</ref>

Cancer Campus is included in one of the main projects for [[Paris]] defined by [[French government]].<ref>{{fr}}[http://www.parismetropole.fr/ressources/actualites/actualites-metropolitaines/article/actualites-de-cancer-campus Le 7 février : Cancer Campus® obtient le label Grand Paris…]</ref> Proposed new public transport systems planned to create a [[metro station]] on the campus.<ref>{{fr}}[http://www.leparisien.fr/le-plan-cancer-campus-prend-forme-13-02-2012-1857959.php Le plan Cancer Campus prend forme]</ref>

Objectives of Cancer Campus are:
* Develop the site of the ''[[Institut Gustave Roussy]]'' and the surrounding area on a surface of one hundred hectares ;
* Constitute a real estate research and [[higher education]], an industrial and services for patients, employees, businesses;
* Create a "citizen space", which analyzes trends and the way society looks at the practices of care and support for patients and makes concrete proposals and partnership to encourage developments in this field, all consistent with the recommendations of the "Cancer Plan".<ref>{{fr}}[http://94.citoyens.com/2012/cancer-campus-lunion-fait-linnovation,31-01-2012.html Cancer Campus : l’union fait l’innovation]</ref>

Cancer campus is managed by a [[voluntary association]] which members are :
* The ''[[Institut Gustave Roussy]]'' and the ''[[Assistance Publique – Hôpitaux de Paris]]'';
* The departement of [[Val-de-Marne]], [[Villejuif]] city;
* The [[Paris Chamber of Commerce]];
* The ''[[Institut Sup'Biotech de Paris]]''.

The ''[[Caisse des dépôts et consignations]]'' is also a partnership, as well as [[Ile-de-France]] region, and the [[business cluster]]s of [[Medicen]] and Génopole.

